<paragraph id="A229FADEB03EF18B5ED5E5943ED8FC4B" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="47253132A8DB90C4F8BF7B957776EEE3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="32C554B5CD658A9CC15E5E5DDD980D21" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="A41B665F18818F2BA0E589DD11428AD1" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a spindly shrub or liana endemic to southern Madagascar. It has small membranous lobed leaves with prominent finer venation clustered on the tips of branches, no more than 3 flowers per inflorescence, and no tufts of trichomes in the axils of the major leaf veins on leaf undersides (domatia). It is the only species of 
<taxonomicName id="48687400210DC66CA2C3A68E6F11578F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FAED080AB382D91758F16A9CBDE771B4" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
endemic to Madagascar not a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="EEF9DFDDB7E491B6438B792563CB8075" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Leptostemonum)" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Leptostemonum">Leptostemonum</taxonomicName>
clade to commonly exhibit lobed leaves (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3C1B0F68C5397D47A56D1FC16B1590D3" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Solanum betroka D'Arcy &amp; Rakot. A Flowering stem B Flowering stem with lobed leaf C Flower D Immature berry E Flower just before anthesis, showing elongate calyx lobes F Simple trichome G Dendritic trichome (Based on: A-D, F, G Bosser 17370; E Leroy 3). Scale bar: A, B = 2 cm; C, E = 7 mm; D = 1 cm; F, G = 0.3 mm. Drawn by Lucy T. Smith." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.66.8457.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/95578" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">5</figureCitation>
) on reproductive stems; lobed leaves in 
<taxonomicName id="78857771AA37C26EA6FF4C7A5B822FA0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum madagascariense" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="madagascariense">
<emphasis id="00383C85D88493996DB23F726C833DB0" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum madagascariense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occasionally occur but are rare.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="54AC3D865C5A3FD7E9E3BE11AE23C450" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="9CA13D3F1981D6926C2622237D1DF30D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="A922CC1DA2B1C75BBDFBC3F797ACCE4D" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be difficult to distinguish from the very similar and possibly closely related 
<taxonomicName id="40CDCD2F6416077F28BF0834441DD134" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum sambiranense" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sambiranense">
<emphasis id="0CD4830D0048A8D2D7F3CB22B7DDC0D9" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum sambiranense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="029E7385A23CF4EE6FF5E02042012906" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum imamense" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imamense">
<emphasis id="90806DF106915E02AED4595822343420" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum imamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="0D10FC4A6F3139ED6FC4EE1AD6805987" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum sambiranense" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sambiranense">
<emphasis id="B8178A440C4166528E52DBB95805B279" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum sambiranense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its ovate to elliptic (versus elliptic to obovate) leaves under 5 cm (versus over 5 cm) long, with cuneate to truncate (versus attenuate) bases, inflorescences with 1-3 (versus 3-10) flowers, and calyx lobes 2-3 mm (versus 4-6 mm) long. 
<taxonomicName id="4E56C2BD161CAAFB1FF9D1410B74DB74" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="D5CE6D9F12AC17B58C3CDC104377BDAF" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears a strong resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="444C29D8E0D32A9C23CDBACFCDBE8580" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum sambiranense" order="Solanales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sambiranense">
<emphasis id="C24F9EF9464C220B51CB64BEFE25EDFE" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Solanum sambiranense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: both have a clearly visible brown fine venation network, membranous 
<pageBreakToken id="95E65CF6E83FC774F5F8A1A390C31609" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" start="start">glabrescent</pageBreakToken>
leaves that dry greenish brown, and a similar habit. Typical representatives of the southern 
<taxonomicName id="EF78C172DB0D8E3D8AD8B3F6DF8A618C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="E9E621DDEF97D2F6DC72823E3F28758F" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and northern 
<taxonomicName id="49559D90E00252C0D6BDFCBA416B42DC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum sambiranense" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sambiranense">
<emphasis id="45A73ADE19D9F46D2CA81676A1451EED" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum sambiranense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clearly distinct but specimens from the centre of Madagascar are more difficult to determine. Further sampling may prove that these two taxa are in fact conspecific. 
<taxonomicName id="CB615ED40DC53621D46CFFE4AAF3E0C2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="190FC44957FE693B6D4CCBF45953FD89" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="40879CF55385FA62FAAB6974C4B42CD2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum imamense" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imamense">
<emphasis id="310D7971361DBE0812EB07F68D216E31" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum imamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its inflorescences with 1-3 (versus 7-13) flowers, flowers under 2 cm (versus over 2 cm) in diameter, and anthers 3.5-5 mm (versus 4-5 mm) long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D7743B16CFC4AF898458C8A3D8EB2BC8" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName id="01B44A78656D59CCAD85C0632F3C3929" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="E91AF0864B43B9425ED095E95611DACD" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been confused with unarmed specimens of the spiny solanums 
<taxonomicName id="693749D3FDA62C51226DC154F7B22F1C" authorityName="W. G. D' Arcy &amp; A. Rakotozafy" authorityYear="1994" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum batoides" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="batoides">
<emphasis id="A985C0B954CE300DDC9432AACE5E501C" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum batoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="89B4BE0B759689007613D3D06EDF5650" originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
&amp; Rakot. and 
<taxonomicName id="97D11FBB73CC70366BD20E96199B730A" authorityName="Boj. ex Dun" authorityYear="1852" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum erythracanthum" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erythracanthum">
<emphasis id="7A00BE3159C9007E8EDE5B6C0708D849" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum erythracanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dunal; these can be distinguished easily based on pubescence and anther morphology. 
<taxonomicName id="A94067C75D10019E809C2B7F6C007081" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="973D8AC6BAA8669919A0B4A1BEAE9E7C" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dendritic trichomes and ellipsoid anthers while 
<taxonomicName id="95016EC6926245CC15E48FED4C35A68C" authorityName="W. G. D' Arcy &amp; A. Rakotozafy" authorityYear="1994" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum batoides" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="batoides">
<emphasis id="F41E0E53E4BBE37E449E02DE4D4AEBEF" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum batoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="454B63CF0DB5AC3BF30B9FEECD37E06D" authorityName="Boj. ex Dun" authorityYear="1852" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum erythracanthum" order="Solanales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erythracanthum">
<emphasis id="6C66F87E11245D4A6748BF48114F2B71" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Solanum erythracanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have 
<pageBreakToken id="386BEF83ACE533F0258828FB15D031D6" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" start="start">the</pageBreakToken>
stellate trichomes and long-tapered anthers typical of members of the 
<taxonomicName id="0EF9D648903CC4BBB6C8C06C40135354" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Leptostemonum)" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Leptostemonum">Leptostemonum</taxonomicName>
clade (
<bibRefCitation id="7A3A1BE8136338A57728CD0F7131D1CB" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" pagination="176 - 193" publicationUrl="10.1111/boj.12053" refId="B108" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Stern, S, Bohs, L, Knapp, S, 2013. African spiny Solanum (subgenus Leptostemonum, Solanaceae): a thorny phylogenetic tangle. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 173: 176 - 193, DOI: 10.1111/boj.12053" title="African spiny Solanum (subgenus Leptostemonum, Solanaceae): a thorny phylogenetic tangle." url="10.1111/boj.12053" volume="173" year="2013">Vorontsova et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="21C6EBFCE9DACB0EFD965377719C4B79" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="A revision of the spiny solanums, Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae) in Africa and Madagascar." pageId="111" pageNumber="112" refId="B107" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Knapp, S, 2016 in press. . A revision of the spiny solanums, Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae) in Africa and Madagascar. 100" volume="100" year="2016">Vorontsova and Knapp 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A7F00F291B26A868D3E08D69542211F" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="D48ACC960882FE327BAF5C9AC7723EA9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="153F52881BEF6B103A48F6DBC849F51E" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs primarily in the unique arid southern ecoregion of Madagascar, with a few records further north in the somewhat wetter western ecoregion (
<bibRefCitation id="33E75F17540724966E60F8E78CC40389" author="Humbert, H" journalOrPublisher="Annales de Biologie" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" pagination="195 - 204" refId="B55" refString="Humbert, H, 1955. Les territoires phytogeographiques de Madagascar. Leur cartographie. Colloque sur les regions ecologiques du globe, Paris 1954. Annales de Biologie 31: 195 - 204" title="Les territoires phytogeographiques de Madagascar. Leur cartographie. Colloque sur les regions ecologiques du globe, Paris 1954." volume="31" year="1955">Humbert 1955</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B6EB3E0193E543C80A23D773973B55F7" author="Faramalala, MH" journalOrPublisher="Universite Paul Sabatier, Toulouse" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" refId="B46" refString="Faramalala, MH, 1988. Etude de la vegetation de Madagascar a l'aide des donnees spaciales. Universite Paul Sabatier, Toulouse" title="Etude de la vegetation de Madagascar a l'aide des donnees spaciales" year="1988">Faramalala 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CC6ED5506C2649BB4161A0350ED4F34F" author="Faramalala, MH" journalOrPublisher="Universite Paul Sabatier, Toulouse" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" refId="B47" refString="Faramalala, MH, 1995. Formations vegetales et domaine forestier national de Madagascar. In: Conservation International (et al.)." title="Formations vegetales et domaine forestier national de Madagascar." volumeTitle="Conservation International (et al.)." year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
). It is the only member of the African non-spiny clade restricted to such severely dry climate, although a few spiny 
<taxonomicName id="124BD8EBFA4F15A464F8EEB1D218B283" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07991FD61B73D9ABC15160C0FCFBC77C" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species also occur in the area: 
<taxonomicName id="7A96BBAD8B1B7C88CEE3F0B35818A1A4" authorityName="W. G. D' Arcy &amp; A. Rakotozafy" authorityYear="1994" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum batoides" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="batoides">
<emphasis id="5F89FF584496499D5770671E2ECBAF12" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum batoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DB26900225F048EA523857CAD871A24D" authorityName="Dun" authorityYear="1852" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum bumeliifolium" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bumeliifolium">
<emphasis id="63FB9BC3256D8151AE933FF23065572A" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum bumeliifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dunal, 
<taxonomicName id="0CEB9CECF421F8B5D8900A04EB6B028F" authorityName="W. G. D' Arcy &amp; R. C. Keating" authorityYear="1976" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum croatii" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="croatii">
<emphasis id="F325C6DF32F379A6EAD0D355432846A7" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum croatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="0FF666A079EBF6E3BF465EBE031AF395" originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
&amp; R.C.Keating, and 
<taxonomicName id="41CB211A4CF04CD485FF38E2B3244183" authorityName="W. G. D' Arcy &amp; R. C. Keating" authorityYear="1976" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum heinianum" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heinianum">
<emphasis id="C8D8C715195893370266B5C90A25C9FE" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum heinianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="7A59BF6406A8B1DED1568CF75999EBC9" originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
&amp; R.C.Keating; the related 
<taxonomicName id="79E57FD9C4F0CB576280D00E56DA6A07" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum imamense" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imamense">
<emphasis id="BF06A3B4BCB8C341829F61190A1B8F7B" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum imamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is partly sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="E47FF422654A928A98090F0B2C47BD71" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="0A79E8BC1219C580A5A32AC2D096DCBF" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the wetter more northern parts of its distribution range. The habitat niche of 
<taxonomicName id="A1FE90A1ABFCC110219B3FD63A09434C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum betroka" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betroka">
<emphasis id="B87F17A3A171430BB948B75E54130938" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum betroka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is significantly different from that of 
<taxonomicName id="66D00CBFD520F2FF6B540A9B92FFBE10" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum imamense" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imamense">
<emphasis id="EDA1452630A56E2856E56B0E0D21BD9C" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum imamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7F64DEAEED2953F46383E6540AAE84E1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum sambiranenese" order="Solanales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sambiranenese">
<emphasis id="6551640E178F932CEC2456E348877863" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Solanum sambiranenese</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both of which occur in wetter habitats further north.. The type collection has smaller leaves with more lobes and denser indumentum than the majority of specimens, and does not exhibit the characteristic pronounced brown venation on dry leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B29EBCF9BCFA1E5214D6234B325DD740" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="B51C22722C26C6367CB5267CC2A3C241" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Selected specimens examined.</paragraph>
